la-pierson-built-the-newsette-wondermind-selena-gomez-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emultimillion-dollar%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Daniella%20Pierson%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20poster%20child%26quot%3B%20for%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20invest%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20she%20aims%20to%20help%20other%20%26quot%3Buninvestable%26quot%3B%20women%20secure%20financing%20for%20their%20ideas%20with%20her%20new%20organization%2C%20CHASM%2C%20where%20she%20wants%20to%20help%20close%20the%20gender%20gap%20in%20VC%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20zero%20investment%2C%20not%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20it.%20I%20wanted%20it%20very%20badly%2C%26quot%3B%20Pierson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20went%20to%20dozens%20of%20VCs%2C%20and%20I%20was%20rejected%2C%20rejected%2C%20rejected%2C%20laughed%20out%20of%20every%20room.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%26quot%3Bhousehold%20name%26quot%3B%20told%20Pierson%20she%20spoke%20too%20much%20and%20too%20quickly%2C%20and%20didn't%20know%20what%20she%20was%20talking%20about%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20cried%20the%20whole%20Uber%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20setbacks%2C%20Pierson%20made%20a%20name%20for%20herself%20with%20her%20newsletter%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounder-newsette-danielle-pierson-built-successful-newsletters-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20Newsette%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20she%20founded%20in%202015%20during%20her%20sophomore%20year%20at%20Boston%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20graduation%2C%20she%20would%20write%20the%20entire%20newsletter%20between%206%20and%2010%20a.m.%2C%20covering%20the%20latest%20news%20in%20beauty%2C%20fashion%2C%20and%20business%2C%20before%20rushing%20to%20classes.%20Then%20she'd%20work%20on%20it%20in%20the%20evenings%20and%20weekends%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20after%20we%20made%20a%20million%20dollars%2C%20I%20still%20wrote%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Pierson%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20have%20fancy%20VC%20money%20to%20fall%20back%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20The%20Newsette%20had%20a%20team%20of%2014%20and%20brought%20in%20revenues%20of%20%2440%20million%20in%20one%20year%20and%20made%20a%20profit%20in%20the%20tens%20of%20millions.%20The%20following%20year%20Pierson%20launched%20another%20newsletter%2C%20Wondermind%2C%20cofounded%20with%20Selena%20Gomez%20and%20the%20actor's%20mother%2C%20Mandy%20Teefey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20year%2C%20Forbes%20named%20Pierson%20the%20world's%20youngest%2C%20wealthiest%20self-made%20woman%20of%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f335302-e60e-4d39-96a1-c5019099cf5d%5C%22%3ENumerous%20barriers%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20Pierson%20more%20than%20five%20years%20of%20hard%20work%20to%20become%20successful%20beyond%20her%20%26quot%3Bwildest%20dreams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPierson%20said%20she%20grew%20up%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20dumb%20twin%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20not%20a%20nickname%20I%20gave%20to%20myself.%20That's%20something%20my%20lovely%20teachers%20and%20peers%20called%20me%20in%20public%20to%20my%20face.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20faced%20numerous%20barriers%20and%20challenges%20as%20a%20female%20entrepreneur.%20She%20failed%20her%20business%20project%20at%20college%20and%20was%20almost%20kicked%20out%20a%20semester%20before%20graduation.%20She%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20OCD%20when%20she%20was%2014%2C%20and%20also%20lives%20with%20ADHD%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPierson%20doesn't%20want%20it%20to%20be%20this%20hard%20for%20other%20women%20like%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fventure-capital-decline-hurts-female-founders-gender-gap-startup-funding-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20amount%20of%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20all-women%20teams%20receive%20is%20low.%20In%202022%2C%20they%20accounted%20for%202.1%25%20(%245.1%20billion)%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%20%3Ca%20href